HEADWORD: Powerable
<hw>Pow"er*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Capable of being effected or accomplished by the application of
power; possible.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>J. Young.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Capable of exerting power; powerful.</def>
<rj><au>Camden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

